[{"_1":2},"routes/puzzle-detail",{"_3":4},"data",{"_5":6,"_7":8},"slug","two-doors","puzzle",{"_5":6,"_9":10,"_34":35,"_36":37,"_38":39},"metadata",{"_11":12,"_13":14,"_15":16,"_19":20,"_21":22,"_26":27,"_28":27,"_29":30,"_31":32,"_33":32},"id","1","title","The Two Doors","concepts",[17,18],"logic","truth-telling","difficulty","easy","tags",[23,24,25],"classic","riddle","starter","dateCreated","2025-10-22T00:00:00.000Z","lastUpdated","credits","A classic logic puzzle\nWritten by Alan\n","preview","The Scenario You find yourself trapped in a dungeon with two doors before you: One door leads to freedom One door leads to certain doom Two guards stand watch:...","websitePreview","content","<h2 class=\"markdown-h1\">The Scenario</h2>\n<p>You find yourself trapped in a dungeon with two doors before you:</p>\n<ul>\n<li>One door leads to <strong>freedom</strong></li>\n<li>One door leads to <strong>certain doom</strong></li>\n</ul>\n<p>Two guards stand watch:</p>\n<ul>\n<li>One guard <strong>always tells the truth</strong></li>\n<li>One guard <strong>always lies</strong></li>\n</ul>\n<p>You don't know which guard is which.</p>\n<h2 class=\"markdown-h1\">The Challenge</h2>\n<p>You may ask <strong>one guard</strong> <strong>one question</strong> to determine which door leads to freedom.</p>\n<p>What question do you ask?</p>\n<details class=\"hint-block\" data-type=\"hint\"><summary class=\"hint-label\">Hint</summary><div class=\"hint-content markdown-content prose max-w-none px-4 py-4 space-y-4\"><p>Think about what happens when you ask one guard about what the other guard would say.</p></div></details>\n<details class=\"hint-block\" data-type=\"hint\"><summary class=\"hint-label\">A More Specific Hint</summary><div class=\"hint-content markdown-content prose max-w-none px-4 py-4 space-y-4\"><p>If you ask the truth-teller what the liar would say, they'll tell you the truth about the liar's lie. If you ask the liar what the truth-teller would say, they'll lie about the truth.</p></div></details>\n<details class=\"solution-block\" data-type=\"solution\"><summary class=\"solution-label\">Solution</summary><div class=\"solution-content markdown-content prose max-w-none px-4 py-4 space-y-4\"><p>Ask either guard: \"If I asked the other guard which door leads to freedom, which door would they point to?\"</p><p>Both guards will point to the <strong>door of doom</strong>:</p><ul>\n<li>The truth-teller will honestly tell you that the liar would point to the door of doom</li>\n<li>The liar will lie about the truth-teller's answer and also point to the door of doom</li>\n</ul><p>Therefore, choose the <strong>opposite door</strong> from the one they indicate.</p></div></details>\n<details class=\"solution-block\" data-type=\"solution\"><summary class=\"solution-label\">Alternative Solution</summary><div class=\"solution-content markdown-content prose max-w-none px-4 py-4 space-y-4\"><p>You could also ask: \"Which door would you point to if I asked you which door leads to freedom?\"</p><p>This works because:</p><ul>\n<li>The truth-teller would point to the correct door (freedom)</li>\n<li>The liar would lie about their own lie, creating a double negative that also points to freedom</li>\n</ul><p>Both guards point to the same door—the door to freedom!</p></div></details>","rawContent","\n# The Scenario\n\nYou find yourself trapped in a dungeon with two doors before you:\n- One door leads to **freedom**\n- One door leads to **certain doom**\n\nTwo guards stand watch:\n- One guard **always tells the truth**\n- One guard **always lies**\n\nYou don't know which guard is which.\n\n# The Challenge\n\nYou may ask **one guard** **one question** to determine which door leads to freedom.\n\nWhat question do you ask?\n\n:::hint\nThink about what happens when you ask one guard about what the other guard would say.\n:::\n\n:::hint[A More Specific Hint]\nIf you ask the truth-teller what the liar would say, they'll tell you the truth about the liar's lie. If you ask the liar what the truth-teller would say, they'll lie about the truth.\n:::\n\n:::solution\nAsk either guard: \"If I asked the other guard which door leads to freedom, which door would they point to?\"\n\nBoth guards will point to the **door of doom**:\n- The truth-teller will honestly tell you that the liar would point to the door of doom\n- The liar will lie about the truth-teller's answer and also point to the door of doom\n\nTherefore, choose the **opposite door** from the one they indicate.\n:::\n\n:::solution[Alternative Solution]\nYou could also ask: \"Which door would you point to if I asked you which door leads to freedom?\"\n\nThis works because:\n- The truth-teller would point to the correct door (freedom)\n- The liar would lie about their own lie, creating a double negative that also points to freedom\n\nBoth guards point to the same door—the door to freedom!\n:::\n","dynamicBlocks",[]]
